<br>
As for all of the hyperboles being thrown around, I'm not sure they help your argument.  In my mind the debate centers around two related main points.<br>
<br>
(1) what is the maximum punishment society should inflict on its criminals?  If you believe that there are absolutely no circumstances where the death penalty should be used as a punishment then there's no need to go to step 2.  You would be in the very small minority of people (most people can think of at least some extreme examples where the death penalty would be justified--e.g. Hitler).  If you're in this camp, there's very little point in debating the topic.  You're not going to convince me that it's never justified and I'm not going to convince you that it's sometimes justified.<br>
<br>
(2)  if there are circumstances that the death penalty is justified, then what level of &quot;comfort&quot; do you require to impose the death penalty.  For some it may be 100% positive proof of guilt of a heinous crime.  In the U.S. the standard is (i) only certain heinous crimes can have the death penalty imposed (ii) guilt proven beyond a reasonable doubt and (iii) a unanimous determination by 12 members of society that the punishment should be the death penalty after considering all mitigating factors.<br>
<br>
I'm comfortable with the standard used in the U.S.  Many people would prefer more of a &quot;comfort&quot; level for the U.S. and cite inadequate public defenders on capital cases, disparate racial makeup for deathrow inmates, and type of execution used. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udenoineanduril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Denoine Anduril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/28/01 8:14:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=627.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lets kill everyone who kills!</span><hr size=1> I read the story of Fish from the web site.<br>
